note: ── Closure-in-loop test ──
note: Creates a function inside a for-each loop that captures the loop variable.
note: Stores each function in a list, then calls them all AFTER the loop ends.
note: Correct (per-iteration binding):  10  20  30
note: Broken (shared-var binding):      30  30  30

set numbers to a list containing 10, 20, 30
set callbacks to a list containing

for each n in numbers:
    create function capture:
        give back n
    end
    callbacks.push with capture
end

note: Call all stored callbacks after the loop has finished
set results to a list containing
for each cb in callbacks:
    set result to cb with
    results.push with result
end

note: Verify each callback captured its own iteration's value
check that results[0] is equal to 10
check that results[1] is equal to 20
check that results[2] is equal to 30

say "Closure-in-loop test passed! Each callback captured its own value."
